        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:22PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Grandjean, or 11 miles southwest of Stanley, moving northwest at 5
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Grandjean around 430 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
